revision.text:
{{unreferenced|date=March 2016}}
[[Mongolian National Broadcaster|MNB Radio 1]], transmitting from [[Ulaanbaatar]], is the only currently licensed station to use 164 kHz for broadcasting. The frequency however is within the 160-190 kHz [[Title 47 CFR Part 15|Part 15]] band authorized by the [[United States of America]]'s [[Federal Communications Commission]], and low-powered stations in the United States may use this frequency to broadcast.

