{{Underlinked|date=October 2016}}
[[File:Awraja of Ethiopia.png|thumb|right|350px|A map of the former Awrajjas of Ethiopia]]
'''Awrajja''' were the third level country subdivisions which subdivided the [[Provinces of Ethiopia]] prior to 1996. Awrajja roughly translates to "county" or "sub-province", and contained a number of "woreda" or districts, the fourth level subdivision of [[Ethiopia]].  In 1996 the Provinces and Awrajja of Ethiopia were replaced with Regions ([[Regions of Ethiopia|Kilil]]) and Zones, and Awrajja ceased to serve an administrative function, though they retain cultural significance.

[[Category:Subdivisions of Ethiopia| ]]


