{{Campaignbox Spanish Civil War}}
The '''Battle of Belchite (1938)''' involving the [[Spanish Republican Army]] took place during the [[Spanish Civil War]]. After the campaigns at Aragón and Quinto, the Lincoln-Washington Battalion marched to the town of Belchite where battalion commander [[Robert Hale Merriman]] ordered the troops to attack the church.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spartacus.schoolnet.co.uk/SPbelchite.htm |title=Belchite |author=John Simkin |date=2007 |accessdate=2 Oct 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004230006/http://www.spartacus.schoolnet.co.uk/SPbelchite.htm |archivedate=2013-10-04 |df= }}</reF> Out of 22 men only 2 survived the first assault. 

