{{Infobox Network | network_name = Hewad Media Group, Hewad TV| network_logo = | country = {{AFG}} | network_type = [[satellite television|Satellite]] [[Television Network]]| available = [[Afghanistan]]| slogan = | owner = Omar | Tel = [+93 744 296 196] | key_people = Ahmad Wali Ahmadi, Hayatullah Masoom, Naser Hotaki, Rohullah Lmar | launch_date = | Other = [https://web.archive.org/web/20110224051858/http://www.hewadtv.com/ https://web.archive.org/web/20110224051858/http://www.hewadtv.com///]| }}
'''Hewad TV''' (meaning ''"Country TV"'' in [[Pashto language|Pashto]]) is a private television station based in [[Kandahar]], [[Afghanistan]]. The channel broadcasts news, shows, and entertainment programs to certain parts of the country. It may expand coverage in the future as [[communications in Afghanistan]] are rapidly growing.
==See also== * [[List of television channels in Afghanistan]] Hewad Hewad was established in 2006. It is owned by Mr. Kazi Mohammad Omar, who also owns AIR. And managed by, Mr. Ahmad Wali Ahmadi. Its 36-40m antenna is located in Shaedanu Chawk in Nawe Shar (“New City”), and its 2.5kW transmitter has a 50km broadcast radius. Through a more powerful transmitter, the plan is to increase both radio and TV coverage. Hewad’s technology is reported to be of a higher standard than that of Kandahar RTA. Hewad broadcasts 20 hours a day, mainly in Pashto (95%). Programming includes music (six hours a week) and local reporting (seven hours a week). Rural areas are also covered, owing to security constraints. Interactive programming includes Shkulai Sahar (“Nice Morning”) and Defeker Tal (“Quiz”). Advertising is broadcast for 20 minutes a day at a price of $50 a minute.
== External links == * [https://web.archive.org/web/20110224051858/http://www.hewadtv.com/ Official site]
