{{Infobox Union |name= Musikerförbundet |country= [[Sweden]] |affiliation= [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] |members= 5600 |full_name= Swedish Musicians Union |native_name= Musikerförbundet |image= [[Image:Swedish Musicians' Union logo.png|125px]] |founded=1907 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Stockholm]], Sweden |people= [[Jan Granvik]], president |website= [http://www.musikerforbundet.se www.musikerforbundet.se] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Swedish Musicians Union''' (Musikerförbundet) is a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It has a membership of 3500 and is affiliated with the [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation]].
==References== *{{cite book | year = 2005 | title = Trade Unions of the World | editor = [[International Centre for Trade Union Rights|ICTUR]] et al., | edition = 6th | publisher = John Harper Publishing | location = London, UK | isbn = 0-9543811-5-7 }}
==External links== * [http://www.musikerforbundet.se Musikerförbundet] official site.
