'''''The Fool of Kairouan''''' ([[Arabic]]: مجنون القيروان ; transliteration: Majnun al-Kairawen; {{lang-fr|Fou de Kairouan}}), produced in 1939, is the first Tunisian musical film, and the first film made in Arabic in Tunisia.<ref>{{cite book |title=Silence, elles tournent: les femmes et le cinéma en Tunisie |last=Gabous |first=Abdelkrim |page=19 |year=1998 |publisher=Cérès |isbn=978-9973-19-387-2 }}</ref> It is starred by the singer [[Mohamed Jamoussi]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Histoire du cinéma en Tunisie |last=Khlifi |first=Omar |page=118 |year=1970 |publisher=Société tunisienne de diffusion |oclc=486898369 }}</ref> It is considered one of the key films in the pre–World War II history of cinema in North Africa.<ref>{{cite book |title=Visions of the East: orientalism in film |last=Bernstein |first=Matthew |author2=Gaylyn Studlar  |page=231 |year=1997 |publisher=[[I.B.Tauris]] |isbn=978-1-86064-304-0 }}</ref>

